Looks like aws trust relationship thing is handled with a policy like this;

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::429942273585:root"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
supporting documentation here: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/cross-acct-access.html
We probably need to add the trust relationship into the policy editor. It looks like the aws console treats it as a separate policy and it doesn't expose the name via the console, but does let you edit the policy text.

testing on the aws console, the policy addition for 3rd party x-acct access is this:
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "sts:ExternalId": "1234567890"
        }
      }
